Abstract: We present here a MAC protocol that is without any framing structure in the control mechanism and built around a "sea of mini-slots". Most of the elements of the protocol have been previously described in one of more of the MAC proposals made to the subcommittee. The performance under both static and highly dynamic loads is close to optimum. The station implementation is particularly simple and the downstream control structure is also simple. It is consistent with most of the decisions so far made in the MAC draft specification. The results given here are for ATM framing, but the algorithm extends very simply to variable length MAC frames. 
